  *5 The Pittsburgh Sleep Quality Index questionnaire is available at www.sleep.pitt.edu/‚Äãinstruments/‚Äã#psqi; for a detailed guide to scoring, see Buysse et al. (1989).

  *6 The Epworth Sleepiness Scale and its scoring can be viewed at www.cdc.gov/‚Äãniosh/‚Äãemres/‚Äãlonghourstraining/‚Äãscale.html.

  *7 The Insomnia Severity Index and information on its scoring and interpretation are available at www.ons.org/‚Äãsites/‚Äãdefault/‚Äãfiles/‚ÄãInsomniaSeverityIndex_ISI.pdf.

  *8 To figure out your sleep chronotype, take the Morningness/Eveningness Questionnaire (MEQ) at https://reference.medscape.com/‚Äãcalculator/‚Äã829/‚Äãmorningness-eveningness-questionnaire-meq.

  *9 The STOP-BANG Questionnaire is available at www.stopbang.ca/‚Äãosa/‚Äãscreening.php.
